result.name: So Bor Kee Restaurant

reviews.text:
It took awhile, but was worth the wait.
Especially recommend the prawns and the clamshells as they were the freshest I’ve had in a long long while.

等恨久，但很好吃。

My favourite seafood restaurant on Cheung chau. They have a wider range of dishes than most of the other seafood places as they also serve sichuan dishes. My first choice in restaurants when I have visitors to the island.
Great seafood at fine prices. Inc spicy fare by chefs from hunan . Grand sunset views

4 dishes for 218 HKD is a steel! The steamed fish had one of the best sauces we've ever tasted. The raiser clams were pretty amazing too. The sichaun prawns were good too and the ginger, although very spicy (obviously) and the spring onion crab was okay but actually we would have gone for something else if we were to eat here again. The blue girl beer is also sold at a good price! Highly recommend!
PS: the tea can be drunk or used to wash your jopsticks, bowl and hands at the end of the meal!
Seafood with super good price, ~$250 for four dishes. As it's a 川菜 restaurant, make sure you order spicy dishes which are the best food of this restaurant
